						<summary>

						<p>Base of the <hi rend="italic">mānastaṁbha</hi> in the Jaina temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 16th century.</p>						

						<p>It states that Buśrēshṭhī of Mahā Ñāgakula had the <hi rend="italic">mānastaṁbha</hi> erected. The record is in Sanskrit.</p>						

						<p>The Tamil version (A. R. No. 517 of 1937-38) engraved on another face of this <hi rend="italic">mānastaṁbha</hi> states that this was the gift of Buśśeṭṭi, son of Bāyi-śeṭṭi, a <hi rend="italic">vaiśya</hi> of Jagatāṇi Gutti.</p>						

						</summary>
